Data Preprocessing

onlineNews <- read.csv("OnlineNewsPopularity.csv",header = TRUE)
onlineNews<-onlineNews[onlineNews[,4]!=0,]
onlineNews <- onlineNews[,-1]
# remove outliers
onlineNews<-onlineNews[onlineNews[,6]<=1,]

#normalze the target variable 
onlineNews$transformed_shares<-log(onlineNews$shares)

attach(onlineNews)
par(mfrow=c(1,2))

# identify fences
IQR<-upperhinge-lowerhinge
lowerouterfence<-lowerhinge-3*IQR
upperouterfence<-upperhinge+3*IQR
print(IQR)
## [1] 1.049822
print(lowerouterfence)
## [1] 3.701719
print(upperouterfence)
## [1] 11.05047
# remove values beyond fences
onlineNews<-onlineNews[!(onlineNews$transformed_shares>=upperouterfence | onlineNews$transformed_shares<=lowerouterfence),]
boxplot(onlineNews$transformed_shares,xlab="Transformed Shares",main="Shares after ouliers removal")

GLM Gaussian From the qqplot we can see y & log(y) is skewed. Anderson-Darling normality test further proved they do not follow normal distribution.

# test normality
library("ggpubr")
## Warning: package 'ggpubr' was built under R version 3.6.2

ggdensity(onlineNews$transformed_shares, 
          main = "Density plot of transformed shares",

ggqqplot(onlineNews$transformed_shares)

          main = "Density plot of shares",
          xlab = "number of shares")

ggqqplot(onlineNews$shares)

# Anderson-Darling normality test
library(nortest)
ad.test(onlineNews$transformed_shares)
## 
##  Anderson-Darling normality test
## 
## data:  onlineNews$transformed_shares
## A = 725.98, p-value < 2.2e-16
ad.test(onlineNews$shares)
## 
##  Anderson-Darling normality test
## 
## data:  onlineNews$shares
## A = 6380.3, p-value < 2.2e-16

Poisson: (for count data): FAIL

lambda.est<-mean(shares) ## estimate of parameter lambda
tab.os<-table(shares)
freq.os<-vector()
for(i in 1: length(tab.os)) freq.os[i]<-tab.os[[i]] # vector of emprical frequencies
freq.ex<-(dpois(0:max(shares),lambda=lambda.est)*200) # vector of fitted (expected) frequencies
acc<-mean(abs(freq.os-trunc(freq.ex)))  # absolute goodness of fit index
## Warning in freq.os - trunc(freq.ex): longer object length is not a multiple of
## shorter object length
acc/mean(freq.os)*100 # relative (percent) goodness of fit index
## [1] 100.0485

gammafit  <-  fitdistrplus::fitdist(onlineNews$transformed_shares, "gamma")
weibullfit  <-  fitdistrplus::fitdist(onlineNews$transformed_shares, "weibull")
lnormfit  <-  fitdistrplus::fitdist(onlineNews$transformed_shares, "lnorm")  

library(flexsurv)
